The '''Madagascan yellowbrow''' ('''''Crossleyia xanthophrys'''''), also known as the '''yellow-browed oxylabes''', is a [[species]] of [[Malagasy warbler]], formerly placed in the family [[Sylviidae]]. Found only in [[Madagascar]], it is the [[monotypic|sole member]] of the [[genus]] ''Crossleyia''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.itis.gov/servlet/SingleRpt/SingleRpt?search_topic=TSN&search_value=557589 |title=ITIS Report: ''Crossleyia'' |publisher=[[Integrated Taxonomic Information System]] |access-date=22 May 2010}}</ref> Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

